Male anal point usually robust, partly parallel­sided with rounded apex and short, stiff lateral setae often directed laterally or even anteriorly; occasionally (
O. nimidens
) anal point broadly triangular and pointed. None to few setae at base on tergite IX; laterosternite IX with several setae . Sternapodeme slightly curved, oral projections well developed. Phallapodeme hooked apically, aedeagal lobe well developed. Virga present and consisting of several small teeth or of cluster of spines or absent. Gonocoxite well developed; superior volsella collar­like or absent; inferior volsella well developed with weak ventral part not extended below dorsal part. Gonostylus with weak to prominent rounded preapical crista dorsalis, megaseta normal.
